defs.docs:
Crate `fst` is a library for efficiently storing and searching ordered sets or
maps where the keys are byte strings. A key design goal of this crate is to
support storing and searching *very large* sets or maps (i.e., billions). This
means that much effort has gone in to making sure that all operations are
memory efficient.

Create a builder that builds a set by writing it to `wtr` in a
 streaming fashion.

defs.name: insert
defs.docs: Insert a new key into the set.

defs.name: extend_iter
defs.value: fn <T, I> (&mut self, iter: I) -> Result<()>
defs.docs: Calls insert on each item in the iterator.

defs.name: extend_stream
defs.value: fn <'f, I, S> (&mut self, stream: I) -> Result<()>
defs.docs: Calls insert on each item in the stream.

defs.name: finish
defs.docs:
Finishes the construction of the set and flushes the underlying
 writer. After completion, the data written to `W` may be read using
 one of `Set`'s constructor methods.

defs.name: into_inner
defs.docs:
Just like `finish`, except it returns the underlying writer after
 flushing it.

defs.name: get_ref
defs.docs: Gets a reference to the underlying writer.

defs.name: bytes_written
defs.docs: Returns the number of bytes written to the underlying writer

defs.name: Stream
defs.docs: A lexicographically ordered stream of keys from a set.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new set stream from an fst stream.

defs.name: into_strs
defs.docs: Convert this stream into a vector of Unicode strings.

defs.name: into_bytes
defs.docs: Convert this stream into a vector of byte strings.

defs.name: StreamBuilder
defs.docs: A builder for constructing range queries on streams.

defs.name: ge
defs.docs: Specify a greater-than-or-equal-to bound.

defs.name: gt
defs.docs: Specify a greater-than bound.

defs.name: le
defs.docs: Specify a less-than-or-equal-to bound.

defs.name: lt
defs.docs: Specify a less-than bound.

defs.name: OpBuilder
defs.docs: A builder for collecting set streams on which to perform set operations.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Create a new set operation builder.

defs.name: add
defs.value: fn <I, S> (mut self, streamable: I) -> Self
defs.docs: Add a stream to this set operation.

defs.name: push
defs.docs: Add a stream to this set operation.

defs.name: union
defs.docs: Performs a union operation on all streams that have been added.

defs.name: intersection
defs.docs: Performs an intersection operation on all streams that have been added.

defs.name: difference
defs.docs:
Performs a difference operation with respect to the first stream added.
 That is, this returns a stream of all elements in the first stream
 that don't exist in any other stream that has been added.

defs.name: symmetric_difference
defs.docs:
Performs a symmetric difference operation on all of the streams that
 have been added.

defs.name: Union
defs.docs: A stream of set union over multiple streams in lexicographic order.

defs.name: Intersection
defs.docs: A stream of set intersection over multiple streams in lexicographic order.

defs.name: Difference
defs.docs: A stream of set difference over multiple streams in lexicographic order.

defs.name: SymmetricDifference
defs.docs:
A stream of set symmetric difference over multiple streams in lexicographic
 order.

defs.name: StreamZeroOutput
defs.docs:
A specialized stream for mapping set streams (`&[u8]`) to streams used
 by raw fsts (`(&[u8], Output)`).

defs.name: Streamer
defs.docs: Streamer describes a "streaming iterator."

defs.name: Item
defs.docs: The type of the item emitted by this stream.

defs.name: next
defs.docs:
Emits the next element in this stream, or `None` to indicate the stream
 has been exhausted.

defs.name: IntoStreamer
defs.docs: IntoStreamer describes types that can be converted to streams.

defs.name: Item
defs.docs: The type of the item emitted by the stream.

defs.name: Into
defs.docs: The type of the stream to be constructed.

defs.name: into_stream
defs.docs: Construct a stream from `Self`.
